# CMS GetAllDataValues (SC 83) response — real frame over plain TCP:8102 (DL/T 2811-2024 §8.3.4).
# Extracted from a real capture (getalldata.pcapng); only the hex is committed, never the pcap. The
# response body is GB/T 33603 "M-coded" (type codes + fixed-width values wrapped in ASN.1 context tags),
# whose exact name/length framing is not fully specified in the available standards, so it is kept verbatim;
# the readable IEC 61850 identifiers (Mod, Beh, Health, NamPlt, PhyNam, Proxy, vendor SWKJ, …) are surfaced
# best-effort as display metadata.

